news.title: Lekhpals to check illegal buildings sprouting in New Noida villages
news.para: To check illegal construction in New Noida, Noida Authority has appointed two lekhpals. They will monitor development across 80 villages and submit weekly reports. This move follows the Master Plan 2041 clearance. The plan envisions New Noida's development in four phases. Land acquisition will be based on mutual consent with farmers. Discussions on compensation rates are ongoing.

news.title: Over 13,200 homes sanctioned for Chenchu tribals across Telangana: Revenue minister
news.para: Telangana's Indiramma housing scheme aims to provide dignity and security to the poor, especially Chenchu tribal women, stated Revenue Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy. Speaking at public meetings, he emphasized the government's commitment to uplifting marginalized communities. A total of 13,266 Indiramma houses will be sanctioned to Chenchu tribals across the state.

news.title: About 50% from Sabarmati riverfront plot rights sale to go to Gujarat government
news.para: Ahmedabad's Sabarmati Riverfront Development Corporation Ltd. (SRFDCL) has approved the sale of development rights for a 4,420 sq m plot for Rs 156.13 crore, with 50% of the revenue going to the state government as per a 2004 agreement.

news.title: NDMC plans to modify allotment and inter pool policy for flats in Lutyens’ Delhi
news.para: The New Delhi Municipal Council (NDMC) is set to revise its flat allotment and inter-pool policy in Lutyens' Delhi due to ongoing issues with officers failing to vacate properties after transfer. This has led to complications in the inter-pooling system and violations of central government housing guidelines.

news.title: Greater Bengaluru blueprint ready, to be tabled in next cabinet meeting: Deputy CM
news.para: Deputy Chief Minister DK Shivakumar announced that a development roadmap for Greater Bengaluru is nearing completion and will soon be presented to the cabinet. This initiative follows the announcement of the Greater Bengaluru Governance Act implementation, aiming to replace BBMP with a new administrative body.

news.title: Lucknow: Registrations for Anant Nagar plan to open on July 11
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority will start registrations for 332 residential plots under Anant Nagar Scheme on July 11. This is the second phase of the scheme. Plots range from 112.5 to 450 square metres. The allotment will be through a lottery system. The scheme spans 785 acres along Mohan Road. It will have wide roads and underground power cabling.

news.title: Chennai civic body issues stop-work notice to Iyra Properties as roads, buildings develop cracks
news.para: Chennai's Greater Chennai Corporation (GCC) halted construction by Iyra Properties in Velachery after significant damage to roads and buildings. Cracks appeared due to improper piling work at the 50,000 sqft site. IIT Madras will assess the damage. Residents reported unbearable vibrations and fear of collapse.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM demands Amaravati land allottees to complete projects on time
news.para: Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister N Chandrababu Naidu has set strict deadlines for construction projects in Amaravati, emphasizing that institutions allotted land must complete them within two and a half to three years. During a review meeting with 72 institutions, including educational, hospitality, and government entities, Naidu assured full support and a single-window system for approvals.

news.title: Signature Global posts ₹2,640 crore pre-sales in Q1 FY26
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) announced pre-sales of ₹2,640 crore for Q1 FY26, a dip from ₹3,120 crore last year, but saw a significant 31% surge in average sales realization, reaching ₹16,296 per sq ft. Chairman Pradeep Kumar Aggarwal expressed confidence in meeting annual targets. Collections for the quarter totaled ₹930 crore, down from ₹1,210 crore.

news.title: Investors snap up growing share of US homes as traditional buyers struggle to afford one
news.para: Real estate investors are increasing their share of US home purchases, reaching a five-year high of 27% in the first quarter. Rising prices and high borrowing costs are sidelining traditional buyers, creating opportunities for investors with cash. While investor purchases have increased, mom-and-pop investors still dominate the market, as institutional investors scale back.

news.title: Ireland cuts minimum apartment standards in bid to boost development
news.para: Ireland's government is set to relax apartment size regulations to stimulate construction, following a 24% drop in apartment building last year. Housing Minister James Browne aims to cut unit costs by €50,000-€100,000, addressing the housing crisis.

news.title: Maharashtra govt tables bill to amend Slum Act to enable SRA to recover transit rent dues from builders
news.para: The Maharashtra government has introduced a bill to amend the law regarding slum redevelopment, empowering the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) to recover pending transit rent from builders. Unpaid rent will be treated as land revenue arrears, enabling the SRA to initiate recovery proceedings.

news.title: Illegal sand mining in Bokaro continues despite NGT ban
news.para: Despite an NGT ban, illegal sand mining persists in Bokaro, particularly at Bhathua Ghat, with minimal enforcement. While the mining department reports seizures and fines, the focus on sand mining remains limited, even as illegal extraction continues unabated.

news.title: Shakti Pumps raises ₹292 crore via QIP
news.para: Shakti Pumps has successfully raised Rs 292.60 crore through Qualified Institutional Placement, issuing 31.87 lakh shares at Rs 918 each. The funds will be used to establish a 2.20 GW solar cell and module manufacturing plant in Madhya Pradesh.

news.title: Lodha Developers raises ₹300 crore via NCDs
news.para: Lodha Developers has successfully secured ₹300 crore through the issuance of 30,000 senior, secured, redeemable, listed non-convertible debentures (NCDs). These debentures, each with a face value of ₹1 lakh, offer an interest rate of 7.96% per annum, payable quarterly.

news.title: About ₹30,885 crore worth of land transacted across India in H1 2025
news.para: India's land market boomed in the first half of 2025. Land transactions surpassed the entire previous year. Deals totaled ₹30,885 crore, potentially generating ₹1.47 lakh crore. Mumbai Metropolitan Region led the activity. Tier 2 and 3 cities are emerging as key players. Residential projects are driving the land demand. Joint development agreements are also on the rise.

news.title: KVN Properties & Assetz Group to develop one million sq ft residential project in Bengaluru
news.para: KVN Properties LLP and Assetz Group have partnered in a strategic development management agreement to develop a residential project in North Bengaluru. This collaboration involves nearly one million sq ft of development, valued at ₹1,000 crore.

news.title: Omaxe to invest ₹1,200 crore to develop 450-acre township in Indore
news.para: Omaxe, via its subsidiaries, is set to expand its footprint in Madhya Pradesh by acquiring a 450-acre land parcel along Indore's Super Corridor. The company plans to develop an integrated township with an investment of ₹1,200 crore, expecting to generate ₹2,500 crore in revenue over three years.

news.title: Davanagere leads in distribution of digitised land records in Karnataka
news.para: Davanagere leads Karnataka's Bhoosuraksha initiative, distributing 13,040 digital land record pages, surpassing Belagavi and Koppal. The revenue department has processed 1.1 crore historical land documents since February 2024, with Davanagere digitizing 52.8 lakh pages alone. Citizens can access these records online for a nominal fee, eliminating physical visits.

news.title: Sobha posts pre-sales of ₹2,078 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Sobha achieved record-breaking real estate sales in Q1 FY26, reaching ₹2,078 crore, driven by strong demand in key markets. Bengaluru and Gurugram led sales, while the successful launch of Sobha Aurum in Greater Noida marked the company's entry into the city. The company delivered 594 residential units and launched two new projects, expanding its footprint across 13 cities.
